 politics, and anthropology to address the goals and problems associated with cultural, religious, and national minority rights. The contributors to this volume explore the conflicts between group demands for cultural autonomy and individual assertions of basic interests. At stake in these debates about rights and autonomy in multicultural and multinational democracies is the very meaning of freedom.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCivil rightszCanada. 0aMinoritiesxCivil rightszCanada. 0aMinoritiesxLegal status, laws, etc.zCanada. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Minority Studies.2bisacsh1 aDeckha, Maneesha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEisenberg, Avigail, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEisenberg, Avigail, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHolder, Cindy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMacleod, Colin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLaren, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcRanor, Shauna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTully, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVallance, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWebber, Jeremy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485512940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774855129423